  <refnamediv>
    <refname>btkSetPointUnit</refname>
    <refpurpose>Modify the label of the selected point</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>btkSetPointUnit(h, type, unit)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>h</term>
        <listitem><para>The handle used to represent an acquisition.</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>type</term>
        <listitem><para>A non empty string to represent the type of the point. Must be a string corresponding to one of the following:
        <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>Marker</listitem>
          <listitem>Angle</listitem>
          <listitem>Force</listitem>
          <listitem>Moment</listitem>
          <listitem>Power</listitem>
          <listitem>Scalar</listitem>
          <listitem>Reaction</listitem>
        </itemizedlist></para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>unit</term>
        <listitem><para>A string representing the new unit.</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Label</title>
    <para>Modify the unit of the selected type.</para>
    <para>By default an acquisition is set with these units:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>Marker: millimeter (mm)</listitem>
      <listitem>Angle: degres (deg)</listitem>
      <listitem>Force: newton (N)</listitem>
      <listitem>Moment: newton millimeter (Nmm)</listitem>
      <listitem>Power: watt (W)</listitem>
      <listitem>Scalar: empty</listitem>
    </itemizedlist></para>
    <para>The acquisition is represented by the handle <literal>h</literal>. This handle is obtained  by the use of a btk* function.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example">btkSetPointUnit(h, 'Moment', 'Nm')</programlisting>
  </refsection>
